# Conversion-volatility test (2026-05-28 PM match diagnosis)
#
# Position captured at TX [95:01.250], 156 plies played.
# White-to-move. White is materially winning (engine peaked at +2865
# cp earlier in the match) but stuck in a conversion-failure shuffle
# pattern that produced a 95-move draw despite the crushing advantage.
#
# Pre-fix observation (binary ef2e153, symmetric pc<=6 hopeless-amp):
#   info depth 2 score cp 3195 nodes 35   ← amp fires at d=2 leaves
#   info depth 3 score cp 905 nodes 93    ← amp doesn't fire at d=3
#   ... -2290 cp swing between adjacent depths in SAME position.
#
# Root cause: symmetric winning-side amp (pc<=6 AND preeg>=+300) fires
# inconsistently at search leaves depending on trade sequences. Engine
# pursues phantom-amped leaves but actual play doesn't deliver pc<=6.
#
# Post-fix expected (this commit, asymmetric amp):
#   - Winning-side amp now requires pc<=2 AND W_Q=1 AND B_Q=0 (narrow
#     54411b4 trigger restored).
#   - In this position, pc > 2 (many pieces still on board).
#   - Therefore winning amp does NOT fire at any leaf — eval is stable.
#   - d=2 through d=5 should report scores within ~100 cp of each
#     other (stable winning signal, no phantom-amped excursions).
#
# Secondary regression check (conditional promotion-survival):
#   - GATE_BLOST_BONUS now only fires when Item-B clamp actually
#     fires (R9 was < preeg before clamp).
#   - Eliminates ADV_PAWN_B double-counting in winning positions.

